# inbox/ is a local processing scratch area. Binary inputs stay
# local; only README.md is tracked.

# Office documents
*.doc
*.docx
*.docm
*.dot
*.dotx

# Spreadsheets
*.xls
*.xlsx
*.xlsm
*.xlsb
*.csv

# Presentations
*.ppt
*.pptx
*.pptm

# PDF and other print-layout inputs
*.pdf

# Archives
*.zip
*.7z
*.rar
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz

# Images (drop into docs/publications/series-assets/ for publishing)
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.bmp
*.tif
*.tiff
*.webp
*.svg

# Raw text exports — keep only if explicitly tracked
*.rtf
*.odt
*.ods
*.odp

# OS cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Explicit allow-list: the README is always tracked.
!README.md
!.gitignore

# inbox/drafts/ subdirectory — agent-authored drafts for iteration.
# Markdown drafts ride on scratch branches without force-add; binary
# formats stay ignored as above.
!drafts/
!drafts/**/*.md

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pandoc bridge outputs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# `make inbox-convert` produces .md siblings for every .docx in the
# inbox. The siblings are governed artefacts (reviewable diffs) and
# should ship with PRs that promote docx sources into canon.
# The original .docx files themselves remain ignored unless explicitly
# allowlisted below.
!**/*.md

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Explicit docx allowlist — uncomment the sources an author wants to
# round-trip through git (e.g., collaborative edits on the binary).
# Default policy: keep .docx local; ship the pandoc-generated .md.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# !AD Computer Object Conversion Guide — Entra ID, Intune, and Azure Arc Governance.docx
# !Git on Windows Server 2025 with IIS — Step-by-Step Implementation Guide.docx
# !UIAO Git Server — Windows Server 2025 with IIS Implementation Guide.docx
# !UIAO Git Infrastructure — Architecture Decision Record.docx
